# AKOS Intent-Ranked Regression (candidate discipline)

Use this rule when a regression should be ordered by **operator-intent value**, not
by mechanical dimension number — the operator's 2026-06-05 framing: *"not mechanical
— take all my intents, use cases, logic, scenarios, interactions, rank them, then
regress."* It is the **value layer** on top of
[`akos-inter-wave-regression.mdc`](akos-inter-wave-regression.mdc) (the structural
safety net), not a replacement for it.

Status: **candidate** (`D-IH-88-F` reserved; canonical CSV registration — pattern
row + process row + CANONICAL_REGISTRY row — is gated on operator approval per
`akos-baseline-governance.mdc`). The skill + runbook + Pydantic SSOT ship now; the
governed-discipline rows land after the gate.

## When this rule applies

- The operator asks for a regression "by what matters / by intent / by value".
- A portfolio-wide health check where operator/agent attention is the scarce
  resource and a flat full-sweep would bury the signal.
- After a multi-phase area buildout (e.g. the Finance F1-F3 cycle) when you want to
  confirm *the goals are still served*, not just *the wiring is intact*.

Out of scope: a single-file change (use the mechanical self-test); a true wave-close
(run the inter-wave 13-dimension sweep — this rule sits above it, not instead).

## RULE 1 — Rank before you run (binding)

Run `py scripts/intent_ranked_regression.py --rank` and sweep surfaces top-down by
Intent Criticality Score. Severity-first surfaces (legal/fiscal + governance
integrity with a known live gap) lead regardless of composite ICS (FMEA
Action-Priority). The full mechanical sweep / `release-gate.py` remains the periodic
safety net (TIA fallback) — never deleted.

## RULE 2 — Attribute every finding (binding)

No finding is reported without an attribution class: **new** (this session's diff),
**pre-existing** (drift predating the session), or **known-deferred** (has an OPS row
+ ETA). "9 failed" is not a result; the ranked + attributed 9 is. Fix-now only when a
pre-existing finding is high-ICS + low-effort + reversible (severity-first); else
defer-OPS with a named owner.

## RULE 3 — Disposition via the 5-option enum (binding)

Reuse the inter-wave enum (rework-now / forward-charter-next / defer-OPS /
accept-as-canon / escalate-to-blocker) per
[`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc). No ad-hoc "fix later".

## RULE 4 — Evidence-only intent weights (binding)

Intent-tier values in `akos/hlk_intent_ranked_regression.py` cite scratchpad / inbox
/ OPS / registry evidence. No evidence, no weight change. Re-derive when the
portfolio shifts materially.

## Either-seat contract

- **Execution seat** (Composer): `--rank` (ordered checklist) + `--self-test`
  (pre_commit circuit-breaker). Mechanical, cheap, repeatable.
- **Thinking seat** (Opus-class): the corpus distillation + attribution + disposition
  judgment per [`intent-ranked-regression-craft`](../skills/intent-ranked-regression-craft/SKILL.md).

